Step 1. Calculate Return on Equity (ROE)

• We use the formula: ROE = (Net Profit) / (Average Owner’s Equity)
• From the balance sheet:
  Beginning Owner’s Equity = Paid-in Capital on 2023-12-31 = 28,000,000.00
  Ending Owner’s Equity = Total Owner’s Equity on 2024-02-05 = 29,938,987.47
  Average Owner’s Equity = (28,000,000.00 + 29,938,987.47) / 2
    = 57,938,987.47 / 2 = 28,969,493.73 (approximately)
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,938,987.47
• Thus, ROE = 1,938,987.47 / 28,969,493.73 ≈ 0.06698, or about 6.70%

Step 2. Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio

• We use the balance sheet “End_amount” values.
• Total Debt (Liabilities) = Total Current Liabilities = 3,143,833.89
• Total Assets = 33,082,821.36
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 3,143,833.89 / 33,082,821.36 ≈ 0.09515, which rounds to 0.10 when expressed to two decimals

Step 3. Calculate Gross Profit Margin

• From the income statement:
  Gross Profit = 6,476,677.56
  Total Revenue = 22,876,677.56
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit) / (Total Revenue) = 6,476,677.56 / 22,876,677.56 ≈ 0.2833 or 28.33%

Presenting the results in the requested JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "6.70%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.10",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.33%"
  }
}
